Lung cancer is caused not by pot or nicotine, but tar, a substance which is absent from high quality pot.<br>
<br>
Fact: The war on drugs is hella expensive.<br>
The money spent on the war on drugs now could be re-allocated in different directions to reduce pot use more effectively if that were the real purpose.  Many analysts conclude that the war on drugs is more about political control in Latin America than drugs<br>
<br>
Fact: Pot is a completely different class of drug from pcp, heroin, or crack.<br>
The addictive properties of pot are relatively low, far below those of caffeine, nicotine, beer or EQ<br>
<br>
Fact: Countries which have legalized pot have a lower rate of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> abuse</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and related deaths<br>
The problem with pot or any substance is abuse.  Yes, pot can be abused, but so can sugar or sex.  The fact that pot is illegal puts a stigma on its use so that people at risk for abuse have a hard time seeking help and recreational users may develop psychological problems from guilt.  Those problems stem not from pot but from societies condemnation of it.<br>
<br>
Fact: Smoking pot doesn't make you a dumbass<br>
You're a dumbass with or without it.  It's a bad idea to smoke and drive just like it is to drink and drive or take sudafed and drive.  <br>
<br>
Fact: Smoking pot can be very relaxing<br>
Many users experience a sense of zen, peace, and connectedness while high.  Pot works to inhibit the processing of data related to social mores, i.e. it makes you feel more free and alters your perception. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/uassmo666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Assmo666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/21/02 6:10:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3103.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmmm . . . .</span><hr size=1> not true actually, pot contains more tar than tobacco. So, over time (a long time) yes it can cause lung cancer.<br>
